  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Basil Mashed Potatoes</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Ew</cat>
        <cat>Text</cat>
        <cat>Import</cat></categories>
      <yield>1</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2 1/2</qty>
          <unit>pounds</unit></amt>
        <item>Baking potatoes,; peeled and cubed</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>3/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Heavy cream</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Stick unsalted butter</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>tablespoons</unit></amt>
        <item>Lemon juice</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Chopped basil leaves</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Grated ginger</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1</qty>
          <unit>tablespoon</unit></amt>
        <item>Minced garlic</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Salt</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  In a large saucepan of salted water bring potatoes to a boil. Simmer about
  20 minutes or until tender. Drain. Pass potatoes through a ricer into a
  mixing bowl. Meanwhile, in a small saucepan combine cream and butter. Bring
  to a boil and keep hot until potatoes are cooked. With a mixer or electric
  beater whip potatoes on slow speed, slowly drizzling in cream mixture. Do
